ional scholarships or financial aid is available.  If you have any dependents, we strongly recommend you get health insurance for them before you arrive in Chicago.     Pay Tuition and fees online         Insurance Fees   All Intensive English Program students are required by the University of Illinois to have health insurance.  Some students have health insurance through their scholarship or program. Our program offers a health insurance policy for F-1 students. The fees for this policy are listed below.  You can pay for this insurance policy online.  Students with other health insurance and students who are not F-1 do not pay for health insurance at the office. However , you must show proof of health insurance valid in the United States.  Your proof of insurance must include:   Name of student  Dates of coverage  Sickness Minimum coverage of $50,000 USD per incident  Injury Minimum coverage of $50,000 USD per incident  In English  U.S. contact information listed (Required only for F-1 students, not citizens or residents.)  Repatriation ($7,800 USD minimum)  Expenses associated with medical evacuation ($10,000 USD minimum)      Pay insurance fees online        F-1 Student Health Insurance Fees through the Tutorium        Full Session  Midterm Entry      Spring  $478  $292    Summer  $375  $215    Fall  $550  $350          Payment Instructions   Payment Deadline  Fees must be paid in full and Scholarship Financial Letters must be received at least one week before the first day of class in order to guarantee registration. Pay tuition and fees online.  Refund Policy  If you cannot attend the session you originally applied for, notify the Tutorium. The nonrefundable application fee can be used for the next I-20 and session only. For future sessions, a new application fee and other documents will be required for registration.  A full refund of fees, excluding the application fee and service charges, is issued if the Tutorium receives notification before the Placement Exam. A partial refund is issued through the second week of class. No refunds are made after the second week of class.  Full Session Refund Schedule   100% refund (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) with notification by the Friday before the Placement Exam  95% by the Friday before classes begin  85% through the first week of classes  65% through the second week of classes    No refunds are made after the second week of classes.  The $175 application fee is non-refundable.   Midterm Entry Refund Schedule   100% refund (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) with notification by the Friday before the Placement Exam  85% through the first week of classes    No refunds are made after the second week of classes.  The $175 application fee is non-refundable.   A processing fee of $300 is required for transfer requests before attending Tutorium classes.    Pay tuition and fees online    Apply to the Intensive English Program            English for International Professionals Tuition     Tuition includes all textbooks and course materials.     Tuition  Course Length      Communication Skills  $575  10 weeks    Speaking Skills for Professionals  $475  8 weeks    Vocabulary and Grammar for Conversation  $600  3 weeks    Online Grammar  $350  5 weeks    Online Writing and Composing  $350  5 weeks          Instructions   No placement test is required to register for these courses. Simply complete our online registration form .  The registration deadline is 1 week before a class begins. Late registration may be possible if there is still space in a course.      Register for your course    Request more information         Refund Policy    100% of your tuition is refunded (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) if you notify us of your withdrawal at least 5 days before the class begins.  95% is refunded (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) if you notify us by 3pm of the Friday before the class begins  85% is refunded (minus the textbook cost) if you notify us before the day of the second class meeting  75% is refunded (minus the textbook cost) if you notify us before the day of the third class meeting  No refunds are issued if you notify us of your withdrawal on or after the day of the third class meeting.  Credit card refunds are processed within 5 business days.  Refunds for check payment may take 6-8 weeks.  If the class is cancelled due to insufficient enrollment, students receive a full refund.           Test Preparation Tuition     Tuition includes all textbooks and course materials.     Tuition  Course Length      TOEFL iBT Preparation  $900  10 weeks    IELTS Preparation  $750  8 weeks    Introduction to the TOEFL and IELTS  $600  3 weeks    TOEFL iBT Practice  $600  3 weeks    IELTS Practice  $600  3 weeks    Online TOEFL Prep: Reading and Listening  $250  5 weeks    Online TOEFL Prep: Speaking  $250  4 weeks    Online TOEFL Prep: Writing  $350  5 weeks    Online TOEFL Prep: Complete Course Package  $850  5 - 10 weeks          Instructions   No placement test is required to register for these courses. Simply complete our online registration form .  The registration deadline is 1 week before a class begins. Late registration may be possible if there is still space in a course.      Register for your course    Request more information         Refund Policy    100% of your tuition is refunded (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) if you notify us of your withdrawal at least 5 days before the class begins.  95% is refunded (minus $20 service fee for credit card payments) if you notify us by 3pm of the Friday before the class begins  85% is refunded (minus the textbook cost) if you notify us before the day of the second class meeting  75% is refunded (minus the textbook cost) if you notify us before the day of the third class meeting  No refunds are issued if you notify us of your withdrawal on or after the day of the third class meeting.  Credit card refunds are processed within 5 business days.  Refunds for check payment may take 6-8 weeks.  If the class is cancelled due to insufficient enrollment, students receive a full refund.              Start your  Intensive English Program Application      Register for  English for International Professionals/Test Prep           Request More Information  Contact us to learn more about the English programs at the Tutorium.   Request Info            How to Apply    Back to main content           Schedule & Start Dates    Tuition & Fees    I-20 & Visa    Transfer Students    Pay Fees                      UIC Logo        The Tutorium         Main Menu    Intensive English    Other Programs    Student Life    About Us    How to Apply      IEP    IEP Courses    IEP Tuition & Fees    IEP Start Dates    Pay Fees    Current Students      More Info    I-20 & Visa    English for International Professionals    Contact Us        Quick Links    Request Information    Apply    Pay Fees         Contact   Tutorium in Intensive English  1333 South Halsted Street, Suite 260 Chicago, Illinois 60607-5019 USA  Phone: +1-312-996-8098  Fax: +1-312-996-4394  tutorium@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts    Facebook    Instagram             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 